content: Fantastic so far. Just wish there was an option to sort based on my own storage format, or at least by publisher...
Still rough, but do support dev. From user of mo*nreader and perf*ectviewer.

Black screen error when reading double page in some comics. No Scrollable double page reading like in comicrack. No comicvine scrapper support No search results from comixology or comicvine instead we paste url why. No Bookmark editing or embedding I can't create TOC like I create in comi
replyContent: Hello, several of the features you mentioned were not added simply because there was no time to develop them. We're talking about features that the Comic Rack itself took years to implement, and as you can see on our PlayStore page, our app has only 8 months of development. Please be patient, for sure a lot of features you requested will be added.

content: This is probably the best offline android reader on the play store. The interface is clean and modern, the library layout is customizable and there is a dark mode! The app also gets updated where as so many other reader apps don't. Would love if there was a search function but other than that this is near perfect for my needs. Was so pleased with the free version that I purchased the pro version within a few minutes. Edit: Found there is a search function!! Use "filter" to search! Awesome!!!

No default right to left reading direction for manga. Why Generate Separate file when editing(embedding ComicInfo.xml) metadata can't we embedded ComicInfo.xml without generating separate file. Black screen error when reading double page in some comics. No Scrollable double page reading like in comicrack. No comicvine scrapper support No search results from comixology or comicvine instead we paste url why. No Bookmark editing or embedding I can't create TOC like I create in comicrack.
Simple, clean, functional. Tried a handful of cbr reader apps and this is by far the best and easiest to use.

Love the app. Got over 900 mangas, but I notice that when I get over a certain amount it forecloses out unless I take some books off the Micros sd. I have a 128gb pretty much full so not sure if that's why?

Excellent comic metadata support, great library interface, fast, supports very large libraries and it has a breadth of different page viewing options. Also very stable and frequently updated. Deserved 5 stars, it is now clearly one of the best options for comics reading on Android.
Great reader app. Have had 0 issues.
By far the best comic reader on Android

Working great with latest update. Only issue I can find is that the dark theme does not correctly change the color of the navigation bar icons on the Tab S7. They should be white, but are in fact dark, which blends into the dark theme, making them hard to see.
Fantastic reader!!

Truly excellent in most ways, but especially in design and speed. It's by far the best looking of all of the readers. I only gave it 4 stars though because there's no way - that I can tell - to mark books as having been read. That's a pretty big omission.
good app, my favorite reader app so far epub support would be great tho

Library syncing still needs improvement as random volumes tend to go missing when syncing a large number of RAR archives. Able to recognize individual folders and map out correctly in an archive like "cover1","cover" etc but individual file names like _01, _02 are not recognized. Thumbnail previews would be nice for page scrolling and needs fixed/sensor for portrait/auto landscape rotation option. Zoom to fill and cover entire screen for manga would be nice to have as well

Clean interface, great performance. There isn't a large quantity of quality cbr/cbz reader apps out there, but this is one of them. This app handles 200+ MB vintage catalog cbz files with ease. I purchased the Pro version to support the developer. Well worth the price. Thank you for a great app!

Best app to read comics in my opinion, with a very nice interface. EPUB support would be a great addition to the app.
Amazing Manga Reader!, great interface, buy it (support the developer) if you like to read manga on your phone!
Awesome app, it's great to see a new decent player in the field of comics reader on Android ! Keep up the good work !
